      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 6:5",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". the actual words of Solomon's speech are more completely given than in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Kings 8:16",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", where the words, \"and I have not chosen a man to be prince over my people Israel, and I have chosen Jerusalem that my name might be there,\" are omitted. For the commentary on this address, see on ",
        "children": []
